article.headline: Hofstra 82, Northeastern 66
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Carlos Rivera and Loren Stokes each scored 21 points and Hofstra routed Northeastern 82-66 on Saturday, extending the Huskies' road losing streak to 15 games. Rivera, who made 7 of 11 shots, also had six rebounds and six assists and four steals for the Pride (18-6, 11-2 Colonial), which led 40-19 at halftime. Stokes, a senior, needs one point to reach 2,000 for his career. Antoine Agudio added 19 points for the Pride. Matt Jannings' 16 points paced the Huskies (7-17, 5-8). Bobby Kelly added 14, and Adrian Martinez had 13. Manny Adako's game-opening basket gave Northeastern its only lead of the game. A 3-pointer from Eugene Spates pulled the Huskies within 26-21 at 9:01 of the first half. Agudio then had six points in a 13-3 run that put the Pride ahead 39-24 with 3:46 left in the half. Jannings had seven points in a 11-2 run as Northeastern closed to 65-59 with 7:39 left in the game. Hofstra closed with a 17-7 run as Agudio and Stokes each had seven points.
